<FlavorTextDefs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../Schema/FlavorText.xsd">

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>LuxarDominion_Warning_CosmicContaminant</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>The Luxar Dominion continues to warn the galactic community against a group they've termed the Cosmic Contaminant. The Dominion describes an organized group of hostile and rapidly changing organisms that thrive in radiation.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>Korath_Declaration_TrueInheritors</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>The Korath Clan has declared themselves the true inheritors of the Drengin Empire. While serving as the Drengin Empire's shock troopers, the Korath became renowned for vicious and ruthless behavior. They've publicly vowed to wipe out all lives.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>Manti_SemiVoluntarySurveys</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>The Manti have begun conducting semi-voluntary surveys. They hope through these surveys to gain a lead on their stolen spawn. Most have found these surveys unintrusive, even if a little rude.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>MimotBrotherhood_BlackMarketSales</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>Black market sales of Mimot-based meals are on the rise. In a public statement, the Mimot Brotherhood condemns buyers and sellers alike.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>Archaeological_Discovery_FestronHiveNetworks</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>Recent surveys have uncovered vast ancient hive networks on several dead worlds. Their resemblance to modern Festron hives is uncanny, leading many to believe that the Festron had a way to traverse space before modern space travel.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>KrynnSyndicate_ReligiousCensusReport</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>The Krynn Syndicate has released its bi-annual religious census report. The report indicates that most conscious life follows The Way. Many independent organizations have already questioned the authenticity of this census report.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>TerranResistance_DocumentaryRumors</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>Rumors indicate that the Terran Resistance is working closely with a galaxy-renowned documentarian to tell their origin story. The documentary is said to paint the Terran Alliance in a poor light. The Alliance has made no public comment in response to the rumors.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>IntueriAggregate_TechnologicalCompetition</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>The Intueri Aggregate attempted to hold its first 'Wonders of Technological Development' competition this week. None attended.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>Xeloxi_CalmDemeanor</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>The Xeloxi are great, and their calm demeanor is an envy to all. It's reported that the Xeloxi are not holding any GNN staff hostage. This "report" is currently unconfirmed.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>DrenginEmpire_KorathClanRelations</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>When asked about their relationships with the Korath Clan, a representative of the Drengin Empire threw a GNN correspondent through a window.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>TorianHeritage_MemorialAnnouncement</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>A heritage organization within the Torian Regime has announced the intent to start a memorial to the Torian's turbulent history and those lost in brutal conditions. Donations from all are welcome.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>DrathFreehold_AllegationsAgainstAltarians</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>The Drath Freehold claims that a recent report published by Altarian historians blatantly ignores obvious facts that prove the Drath originated from Altar. As of yet, no independent review has supported this claim.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

    <FlavorTextDef>
        <InternalName>PhalenoidsAdvance_NocturnalCycleTraditions</InternalName>
        <FlavorTextOption>
            <Requirements>
                <ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>false</ListenerHasUniversalTranslator>
                <PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>false</PlayerMustKnowSpeaker>
                <PlayerMustKnowListener>true</PlayerMustKnowListener>
            </Requirements>
            <Text>A cultural group from within the Phalenoids Advance has happily shared their traditions around the Nocturnal Cycle, with celebrations occurring roughly once every 15 months. They encourage any interested to participate in their ceremonies.</Text>
        </FlavorTextOption>
    </FlavorTextDef>

